system:
The Twelve Caesars is a work of ancient Roman history written by the Roman historian Suetonius in the early 2nd century AD. It is a biographical work that describes the lives and reigns of Julius Caesar and the subsequent emperors of the Roman Empire, known as the Julio-Claudian dynasty.

Suetonius was a Roman historian and court official who worked under the emperor Hadrian. He was born in 69 AD and died in 140 AD. He was educated in rhetoric and law and eventually rose to become a consul, a high position in the Roman government. He wrote The Twelve Caesars while working as a secretary to Hadrian, and it became one of his most famous works.

The Twelve Caesars was written as a collection of biographies of each of the Julio-Claudian emperors, beginning with Julius Caesar and ending with Nero. Suetonius wrote the biographies in a chronological order, starting with Julius Caesar and ending with Nero, each one covering the life and reign of each emperor.

Suetonius's writing style is known for its vivid details and anecdotes about the emperors' personal lives, including their physical appearance, habits, relationships, and political struggles. He also included information about their achievements, such as military victories or building projects, as well as their failures and scandals.

Overall, The Twelve Caesars is an important work of ancient Roman history that provides valuable insights into the lives and reigns of some of the most influential figures in Roman history.

prompt: ### Human: "Vinsamlegast segðu mér sögu Walt Disney."### Assistant:
system:
"Walt Disney fue un creador de múltiple empresas de entretenimiento, un inventor, un productor, un animador y un director de cine estadounidense. 

Hijo de un agricultor en Chicago, Walt Disney empezó su carrera profesional como animador con el estudio de animación Laugh-O-Gram en Kansas City, Missouri, donde creó su personaje más famoso, Oswald el conejo afelpado. La compañía fue cerrada cuando no pudo pagar sus deudas y Walt regresó a California. 

En California, Disney fundó con su hermano Roy Disney la compañía Laugh-O-Gram Films, que en 1923 se convirtió en Walt Disney Productions. El año siguiente creó su primer largometraje animado, Alice's Wonderland, que no tuvo éxito. 

Disney, Roy y su hermano Roy O. fueron contratados para realizar una serie animada basada en los cuentos de hadas de los hermanos Grimm y Hans Christian Andersen para el United States Post Office Department. Debido a la falta de éxito en la venta de la serie, los hermanos decidieron comenzar una nueva serie animada con cortometrajes que finalmente llevaron a la producción del primer largometraje animado totalmente sonoro, Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs (1937). 

En 1955 Disney fundó con sus sobrinos Roy Edward Disney y Richard Irving Miller la empresa Buena Vista Film Distribution Company (ahora conocida como The Walt Disney Studios). El primer largometraje animado en ser distribuido por la empresa fue Cinderella (1950). Después de la muerte de Walt Disney en 1966, Buena Vista se convirtió en el principal distribuidor de películas de Walt Disney Pictures.

prompt: ### Human: "Halló, ég vil læra að baka challah. Getur þú gefið mér uppskrift fyrir það?"### Assistant:
system:
"Sure thing! Here's a simple recipe for challah bread:

Ingredients:

• 1 pound (450 grams) all-purpose flour
• 1 teaspoon (5 grams) sugar
• 1 teaspoon (5 grams) salt
• 1 egg
• 1 tablespoon (15 ml) warm water
• 1 tablespoon (15 ml) oil
• 2 teaspoons (10 grams) yeast
Instructions:

1. In a large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, salt, and egg. Add the warm water and oil and stir until combined.
2. Add the yeast to the mixture and stir until dissolved. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and let it sit in a warm place until it doubles in size, about 2 hours.
3. Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C) and grease a baking sheet.
4. Knead the dough on a lightly floured surface for about 10 minutes, until it is smooth and elastic. Place the dough in a greased bowl, cover it with plastic wrap, and let it rise until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
5. Punch down the dough and divide it into two equal pieces. Shape each piece into a long loaf and place them on the prepared baking sheet. Let them rise until they are almost doubled in size, about 45 minutes.
6. Brush the loaves with melted butter and sprinkle them with poppy seeds or sesame seeds if desired. Bake the challah for about 25-30 minutes, or until golden brown and cooked through. Let the bread cool completely before slicing and serving.

prompt: ### Human: "Hvar er Indónesía?"### Assistant:
system:
Indonésie est un pays d'Asie du Sud-Est situé au sud de la mer de Chine méridionale. Indonésie est un archipel d'environ 17 508 îles. Sa capitale est Jakarta. La langue officielle est l'indonésien, qui appartient au groupe des langues austronésiennes et est proche du malais, du javanais et du balinais.

Indonésie a une population de plus de 270 millions d'habitants et une superficie de 1 904 569 km². Les principaux pays voisins sont le Timor oriental, l'Inde, le Bangladesh, la Malaisie et les Philippines. La religion dominante est l'islam, mais le christianisme, le bouddhisme et l'hindouisme sont également présents.

L'économie d'Indonésie est fortement centrée sur l'agriculture, avec des productions importantes de riz, de palme à huile, d'élevage de bovins, d'aviculture et de poissons. Les principales ressources naturelles d'Indonésie incluent du pétrole et du charbon. Le pays possède également des richesses minérales, notamment en cuivre, en fer, en nickel et en or.

La géographie d'Indonésie est variée avec des montagnes, des plaines côtières et des plateaux. L'île de Sumatra abrite le mont Kerinci, qui est le point culminant du pays avec une altitude de 4 884 mètres. D'autres îles importantes sont Java, Sulawesi et Kalimantan.

Les principales villes d'Indonésie sont Jakarta (la capitale), Surabaya (la plus grande ville), Bandung (le centre industriel) et Denpasar (la capitale provinciale de Bali). Le tourisme est également important pour l'économie du pays avec des sites comme Borobudur (le temple bouddhiste le plus grand au monde) et Gili Trawangan (une île touristique près de Lombok).

En matière de culture, Indonésie a une longue histoire avec une influence importante dans le monde malais. Le gouvernement a entretenu un programme culturel ambitieux depuis les années 2000 pour promouvoir les arts traditionnels indonésiens et encourager le développement économique à travers la culture.

La langue indonésienne est utilisée dans tous les domaines professionnels et éducatifs. Les médias locaux incluent plusieurs chaînes de télévision nationales ainsi que plusieurs journaux nationaux en langue indonésienne. Les sports populaires en Indonésie comprennent notamment le football et le badminton.
source: "Hvar er Indónesía?"

system:
"Skyr" är ett isländskt gott som är baserat på fjällkost. Skyr är en variant av fermenterad viltkost, ofta gjord av getmjölk. Det är en blandning av skummjölk och getmjölk, som har blivit fermenterad och torkad.

Skyr grunnatriðin är en metod för att framställa skyr från början. Den består av tre steg:

1. Uppföra geten: Du ska uppföra en ko och hålla den i ett fält med andra koar. För att förbereda ditt landskap, lägger du ner lera i en lång, bred träbricka, som du kan hänga på fästet.
2. Utvinna mjölk: Nu ska du uppföra en liten håla på din gård, där du kan samla mjölk från koarna när de betar. Därefter kan du tillverka getmjölk genom att filtrera mjölken i en speciell filtreringskanna.
3. Fermentera mjölken: Nu ska du kunna samla in skummjölken från mjölken och koka den i en liten kittel på ett mindre eldstadium. Eftersom skummjölken bara kan samlas in efter några timmar eller dagar efter att det har blivit färskt, är det viktigt att du ständigt observerar den och tömmer ut den när den kokar över.

Om du vill tillverka omätligt flata skyr, ska du först ta bort mjölet från skummjölken innan du kokar den i kitteln, och sedan hälla resten av mjölet till det som kokas i kitteln. Därefter ska du låta det koka tills det blir svart och visst är det rätta temperaturer för detta; sedan kan du tillverka omätligt flat skyr genom att fylla upp en halv soppa med det som kokats i kitteln. Eftersom det går så fort att göra omätligt flat skyr, så är det vanligt att använda den för olika former av pasta eller pastischips.

Skyr ummál är också ett isländskt gott som kan användas i olika recept på isländsk mat, men som också används för att baka pajer och desserter. Det består av äggvita och stärkelse som har blandats ihop och sedan lagrats för en längre tid tills de har blivit små stora pajer eller desserter. Dessa dessertpajer kan vara så små som vad som helst, från de mest små till de största möjliga pajerna; dock är det vanligt att man använder små pajer då de går så fort att baka och läggas in i olika pajerserviser. Ummal består av två delar: 1) äggvita; 2) stärkelse (eller andra flisor). Du ska först kombinera äggvita och stärkelse tillsammans, men senare ska du lägga dem i olika temperaturer för att ge dem olika egenskaper: äggvita måste vara lufttorkad under omgångar för att få den rätta texturen; därefter ska man värma upp äggvitan till den härdade temperaturen; senare ska man ta bort äggvitan från värmen medan man värmer upp stärkelserna till just rätt temperaturen; slutligen måste man värma upp äggvitan igen till rätt temperatur för att sedan läggas in i dessernterna (eller andra recept).

Skyr grunnatriðin är vanligtvis färdig efter tre dagar (men även mer), men skyr ummál tar ofta längre tid än detta - från två dagar till ett par veckor (men även mer). Det finns många andra varianter av dessertern som man kan åstadkomma genom att bara ändra på receptet, men ummál

```python
# Integral using Trapezoidal Rule
def trapezoidal_rule(func, lower, upper, n):
    # Calculate the left hand side of the subdivisions
    x_l = (lower + upper) / 2
    x_r = lower
    x = np.linspace(x_l, x_r, n)

    # Calculate the function values at each subdivision
    y_l = func(x_l)
    y_r = func(x_r)
    y = np.concatenate(([y_l], y_r))

    # Calculate the difference between function values and the subdivisions
    f_difference = (y_r - y_l) / (x_r - x_l)
    b_difference = (y_r - y) / (x - x_r)
    f = np.concatenate(([f_difference], b_difference))
    
    # Calculate the integral using trapezoidal rule as an average of the difference between the function values and the subdivisions. 
    return np.average(f)
```

The blue whale's body is streamlined for speed and is covered in a thick layer of blubber that insulates it from the cold water and provides buoyancy. It has large eyes that are located on the sides of its head, which allow it to see well in both directions, and its mouth is located at the end of its long, slender snout.

The blue whale feeds on krill, small shrimp-like crustaceans that live in large swarms near the ocean surface. Blue whales are able to filter large amounts of water and krill through their baleen plates, which are made of keratin, the same material that makes up human hair and nails. They then swallow the krill whole, without chewing.

Blue whales live in all the world's oceans, but they are most commonly found in polar regions such as the Antarctic Ocean and the Southern Ocean. They can be found alone or in small groups, and they communicate with each other using low-frequency sounds that can travel great distances underwater.

Blue whales are endangered due to human activities such as commercial whaling and climate change, which can affect their food supply and habitat. The International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) has classified blue whales as endangered on its Red List of Threatened Species.

His ideas have been used to challenge traditional ways of thinking and to inspire new ways of understanding the world. Some of the most notable ways in which Nietzsche's ideas have influenced contemporary thought include:

1. Critiques of religion: Nietzsche's critiques of religion have been especially influential in the secularization of Western society. His arguments that religion is a product of human desire and fear, rather than a reflection of divine truth, have challenged the idea that religion is necessary for morality and social order.

2. Critiques of morality: Nietzsche's critique of morality has also been influential in shaping contemporary thought. His idea that morality is a set of values that are imposed on us by society, rather than being inherent in human nature, has challenged the idea that moral values are objective or universal.

3. Critiques of power: Nietzsche's critique of power and its abuse has also been influential in contemporary thought. His idea that power is inherently corrupting and that those who wield power are more likely to abuse it has inspired many works of literature, film, and art that explore the nature of power and its consequences.

4. Critiques of traditional values: Nietzsche's critiques of traditional values, such as his idea that "God is dead" and that we should embrace our own individuality and creativity, have inspired many artists and thinkers to challenge traditional ways of thinking and to explore new ways of living.

In conclusion, Nietzsche's works have had a significant impact on contemporary thought and culture by challenging traditional ways of thinking and inspiring new ways of understanding the world. His critiques of religion, morality, power, and traditional values continue to influence contemporary thought and culture in a variety of ways.
